<p>Is there a tool or any kind of best-practice to manage dependencies in relation to software architecture/ design in large scale Java EE projects? The challenge we have is to document, which library/ framework is allowed to use. And the usage scenario depending on the architecture/ layer, customer deployment etc must be clear also. E.g. Usage of X for REST-Services, Usage of Y only in Component A, Utility Z for Collections, Usage of xyz allowed for internal use like testing but not for customer deployments and so on ...</p>